'Submit' button in HTML Post a reply
14 posts	• Page 1 of 2 • 1, 2	'Submit' button in HTML
by RabbitH0le on Wed Sep 29, 2010 5:14 pm	([msg=46786]see 'Submit' button in HTML[/msg])
Quick question. I'm tinkering around with HTML forms on my test website. I'm trying to make a virtual guest book that includes Name and E-mail inputs and has a Submit button to submit the data. I don't quite understand where this data goes after it is submitted, and how I am supposed to retrieve it. Can I get it to flow to a text file of some sort?Here is the code I have now:<form name="input" action="" method="get">Username: <input type="text" name="user" />E-mail: <input type="text" name="email" /><input type="submit" value="Submit" /></form>
