E-mail	Re: 'Submit' button in HTML
by Goatboy on Wed Sep 29, 2010 5:18 pm	([msg=46787]see Re: 'Submit' button in HTML[/msg])
You can't make a guestbook entirely in HTML. Like you said, there needs to be something to handle the input. This "something" is probably wither ASP or PHP. Perl, Python, and just about any other language can handle it, but ASP and PHP are the two most commonly associated with server-side web code.
